## Should This Be a Plugin?

Build a plugin if: the feature runs persistently, hooks into core lifecycle events, and multiple unrelated users would need it in roughly the same form.

Write a one-off script instead if: it is a one-time migration, specific to one site, or an agent can generate it correctly from the schema alone.

## File Structure

```
plugins/my-plugin/
  index.ts          # Required. Exports a named const implementing PugmillPlugin.
  manifest.json     # Required. Plugin metadata.
  schema.ts         # Optional. Drizzle table definitions.
  db.ts             # Optional. Query helpers.
  actions.ts        # Optional. Next.js server actions.
  components/       # Optional. React components for slots or the admin page.
```

## manifest.json

```json
{
  "id": "my-plugin",
  "name": "My Plugin",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "One-line description shown in the admin UI."
}
```

The id must match the directory name and use only [a-z0-9-].

## Installation Contract (4 Steps)

STEP 1 — Create /plugins/<plugin-id>/index.ts and manifest.json.

STEP 2 — Add a static import in src/lib/plugin-registry.ts:
```typescript
import { myPlugin } from "../../plugins/my-plugin/index";
```

STEP 3 — Add to ALL_PLUGINS array in src/lib/plugin-registry.ts.

STEP 4 — Activate via admin UI (/admin/plugins) or add id to config.modules.activePlugins.

## PugmillPlugin Interface

```typescript
import type { PugmillPlugin } from "../../src/lib/plugin-registry";

export const myPlugin: PugmillPlugin = {
  id: "my-plugin",
  name: "My Plugin",
  version: "1.0.0",
  description: "Does something useful.",

  settingsDefs: [],      // optional — drives the settings UI
  schema: {},            // optional — only if plugin needs DB tables
  slots: {},             // optional — frontend UI injection points
  adminPage: MyAdminPage, // optional — custom admin screen
  actionHref: "/admin/my-plugin", // optional — sidebar sub-nav entry

  async initialize(hooks, settings) {
    // Register hook listeners here.
  },

  destroy() {
    // Called on clean server shutdown. Safe to omit.
  },
};
```

## Settings (settingsDefs)

```typescript
settingsDefs: [
  {
    key: "apiKey",
    label: "API Key",
    type: "text",       // "text" | "boolean" | "select"
    default: "",
    description: "Your service API key.",
    secret: true,       // masks value in admin UI
    required: true,
  },
  {
    key: "mode",
    label: "Mode",
    type: "select",
    default: "auto",
    options: ["auto", "manual"],
  },
],
```

Settings are passed into initialize() already resolved (defaults merged with saved values):
```typescript
async initialize(hooks, settings) {
  const apiKey = settings.apiKey as string;
}
```

## Database Schema

Naming rule: plugin_<plugin-id>_<tablename>.
No FK constraints to core tables — store IDs as plain integers.
migrate() must be idempotent (IF NOT EXISTS). Runs on every cold start.

```typescript
// schema.ts
export const pluginMyPluginItems = pgTable("plugin_my_plugin_items", {
  id: serial("id").primaryKey(),
  postId: integer("post_id").notNull(),  // plain integer, no FK
  content: text("content").notNull(),
  createdAt: timestamptz("created_at").notNull().defaultNow(),
});

// In index.ts
schema: {
  async migrate() {
    await db.execute(sql`CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS plugin_my_plugin_items (...)`);
  },
  async teardown() {
    await db.execute(sql`DROP TABLE IF EXISTS plugin_my_plugin_items`);
  },
},
```

## Frontend Slots

Slots inject React components into theme pages without the theme importing the plugin directly.

Available slots:
- postFooter — below post content. Props: { postId: number; postSlug: string }
- siteBanner — on every page, after the layout. Props: { settings: PluginSettings }

```typescript
slots: {
  postFooter: MyPostFooterComponent,
  siteBanner: MySiteBannerComponent,
},
```

## Custom Admin Page

Provide an adminPage Server Component. It renders at /admin/plugins/<plugin-id>.
When adminPage is set, the inline settings panel is hidden from the plugin card.

```typescript
import { db } from "../../../src/lib/db";

export default async function MyAdminPage({ searchParams }) {
  const items = await db.select().from(pluginMyPluginItems);
  return <div>{/* render items */}</div>;
}
```

## Sidebar Sub-Nav

actionHref causes the plugin to appear as a sub-section in the admin sidebar with unread notification counts.

## Notifications

```typescript
import { createNotification } from "../../src/lib/notifications";

hooks.addAction("post:after-publish", async ({ post }) => {
  await createNotification({
    pluginId: "my-plugin",
    type: "info",   // "info" | "warning" | "error"
    message: `"${post.title}" was published.`,
    href: `/admin/posts/${post.id}`,
    replaceKey: `published:${post.id}`,  // upserts instead of inserting
  });
});
```

Use replaceKey for aggregate counts (e.g. '5 items pending') to update in place.

## Server Actions

All exported plugin server actions MUST call await loadPlugins() at the top.

```typescript
// plugins/my-plugin/actions.ts
"use server";
import { loadPlugins } from "../../src/lib/plugin-loader";
import { getCurrentUser } from "../../src/lib/get-current-user";

export async function myPluginAction(formData: FormData) {
  await loadPlugins();
  const user = await getCurrentUser();
  // ...
}
```

## Conventions

- No plugin-to-plugin imports. Use shared hooks for inter-plugin communication.
- Table naming: plugin_<plugin-id>_<tablename> — no exceptions.
- No FK constraints to core tables.
- Hook names must come from ActionCatalogue / FilterCatalogue in hook-catalogue.ts.
- Secrets in settings: set secret: true. Never log them.
- initialize() is for registering listeners, not running queries on every request.

## Naming Convention

namespace:event — e.g. post:after-save
namespace:sub:event — e.g. api:post:response

All hook names use lowercase with colons as separators.

## Action Hooks

```typescript
hooks.addAction("post:after-save", async ({ post }) => { ... });
```

Standard actions: errors are caught and become admin notifications. The calling operation is never blocked.

Strict actions: the listener MAY throw to abort the operation. The thrown message is shown to the user.

| Hook | STRICT | Payload |
|---|---|---|
| post:after-save | | { post: PostPayload } |
| post:before-delete | | { postId: number } |
| post:after-publish | | { post: PostPayload } |
| media:after-upload | | { file: MediaPayload } |
| media:after-delete | | { fileId: number } |
| user:after-login | | { user: UserPayload } |
| user:after-logout | | { userId: string } |
| comment:before-create | YES | { comment: CommentDraft } |
| comment:after-create | | { comment: CommentPayload } |
| comment:after-approve | | { commentId: number; approved: boolean } |
| consent:after-accept | | { categories: { essential: true; nonEssential: boolean } } |
| consent:after-update | | { categories: { essential: true; nonEssential: boolean } } |

## Filter Hooks

```typescript
hooks.addFilter("content:render", ({ input, post }) => {
  return input + "\n\n*Appended by plugin.*";
});
```

Filters MUST return a value of the same type as input.

| Hook | Input type | Payload |
|---|---|---|
| content:render | string | { input: string; post: PostPayload } |
| content:excerpt | string | { input: string; post: PostPayload } |
| nav:items | NavItem[] | { input: NavItem[] } |
| head:meta | MetaTag[] | { input: MetaTag[]; post?: PostPayload } |
| api:post:response | Record<string, unknown> | { input: Record<string, unknown>; post: PostPayload } |

## Payload Types

```typescript
interface PostPayload {
  id: number; slug: string; title: string;
  type: "post" | "page"; published: boolean;
  authorId: string | null; parentId: number | null;
  createdAt: Date; updatedAt: Date;
}

interface MediaPayload {
  id: number; url: string; fileName: string;
  fileType: string | null; fileSize: number | null;
  storageKey: string | null; uploaderId: string | null;
}

interface UserPayload {
  id: string; email: string; name: string | null; role: string;
}

interface CommentDraft {
  postId: number; authorName: string; authorEmail: string;
  content: string; parentId?: number;
}

interface CommentPayload extends CommentDraft {
  id: number; approved: boolean; parentId: number | null; createdAt: Date;
}

interface NavItem { label: string; path: string; [key: string]: unknown; }
interface MetaTag { name?: string; property?: string; content: string; }
```

## Dispatching from Core

```typescript
await hooks.doAction("post:after-save", { post });           // standard
await hooks.doActionStrict("comment:before-create", { comment }); // strict — re-throws
const content = await hooks.applyFilters("content:render", { input: raw, post }); // filter
```

## File Structure

```
themes/my-theme/
  manifest.json     # Required
  Layout.tsx        # Required
  design.ts         # Required
  views/
    HomeView.tsx    # Required
    PostView.tsx    # Required
    PageView.tsx    # Required
  components/       # Optional
```

## Installation Contract (6 Steps)

STEP 1 — Create the theme directory.

STEP 2 — Add theme id to THEME_ALLOWLIST in src/lib/theme-registry.ts:
```typescript
export const THEME_ALLOWLIST = ["default", "my-theme"] as const;
```

STEP 3 — Add static imports to src/lib/theme-modules.ts. Static imports are required — Turbopack cannot analyze dynamic template-literal imports.

STEP 4 — Add theme to ALL_THEMES in src/lib/theme-registry.ts.

STEP 5 — Activate via admin UI (Design → Themes) or set config.appearance.activeTheme.

STEP 6 — Create design.ts (required for the Design admin page to work).

## design.ts — Required Exports

| Export | Type | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| DESIGN_TOKEN_DEFS | DesignTokenDef[] | Token definitions — drives the Design admin UI |
| DESIGN_DEFAULTS | Record<string, string> | Default value for every token key |
| SANS_FONTS | string[] | Allowlist of sans-serif Google Fonts |
| MONO_FONTS | string[] | Allowlist of monospace Google Fonts |
| buildCssString | function | Converts token values → :root { --var: value; } CSS |
| buildGoogleFontsUrl | function | Builds Google Fonts stylesheet URL from active fonts |

## DesignTokenDef Shape

```typescript
import type { DesignTokenDef } from "../../src/types/design";

{
  key: "colorAccent",           // unique key — used in DESIGN_DEFAULTS and config
  label: "Accent Color",        // shown in admin UI
  description: "Primary brand color.",
  type: "color",                // "color" | "google-font"
  group: "colors",              // groups tokens into sections in admin UI
  cssVariable: "--color-accent",// injected as CSS custom property
  default: "#2563eb",
  editable: true,               // false = hidden from admin UI
  order: 1,                     // display order within group
}
```

## Layout.tsx Pattern

```typescript
import { getConfig } from "@/lib/config";
import { sanitizeThemeName } from "@/lib/theme-registry";
import { getDesignConfig } from "@/lib/design-config";
import { buildCssString, buildGoogleFontsUrl, DESIGN_TOKEN_DEFS } from "./design";
import { getActiveSlots } from "@/lib/plugin-registry";
import { cookies } from "next/headers";

export default async function ThemeLayout({ children }) {
  const config = await getConfig();
  const themeId = sanitizeThemeName(config.appearance.activeTheme);
  const cookieStore = await cookies();
  const isPreview = cookieStore.get("__pugmill_design_preview")?.value === "1";
  const designConfig = await getDesignConfig(themeId, isPreview ? "draft" : "published");
  const cssString = buildCssString(designConfig, DESIGN_TOKEN_DEFS);
  const fontUrl = buildGoogleFontsUrl(designConfig);
  const siteBanners = getActiveSlots("siteBanner", config.modules.activePlugins, config.modules.pluginSettings ?? {});

  return (
    <div style={{ fontFamily: "var(--font-sans)", backgroundColor: "var(--color-background)" }}>
      <style dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: cssString }} />
      {fontUrl && <link rel="stylesheet" href={fontUrl} />}
      <main>{children}</main>
      {siteBanners.map(({ pluginId, Component, settings }) => (
        <Component key={pluginId} settings={settings} />
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}
```

## PostView.tsx Pattern

Content arrives as a Markdown string. The view renders it and handles postFooter slots.

```typescript
import ReactMarkdown from "react-markdown";
import remarkGfm from "remark-gfm";
import rehypeRaw from "rehype-raw";
import rehypeSanitize, { defaultSchema } from "rehype-sanitize";

// Always pass through rehypeSanitize — the content:render filter hook allows
// plugins to append HTML, and sanitization prevents XSS.
<ReactMarkdown remarkPlugins={[remarkGfm]} rehypePlugins={[rehypeRaw, rehypeSanitize]}>
  {content}
</ReactMarkdown>
```

## CSS Custom Properties

Always reference design tokens via CSS custom properties. Never hardcode colors or fonts.

```typescript
// Inline style (always works)
<div style={{ color: "var(--color-foreground)", background: "var(--color-background)" }}>

// Tailwind arbitrary value
<div className="text-[var(--color-foreground)] bg-[var(--color-background)]">
```

## Conventions

- Server Components by default. Add 'use client' only when interactivity is required.
- No direct plugin imports. Use getActiveSlots() to render plugin UI.
- No hardcoded colors or fonts. Always use CSS custom properties.
- sanitizeThemeName() must gate any dynamic theme reference.
- The theme id is immutable after install — it keys the theme_design_configs table.

## Overview

Site configuration is stored as a single JSONB row in the site_config table (id=1). Access it via getConfig() from @/lib/config.

## API

```typescript
import { getConfig, updateConfig } from "@/lib/config";

// Read — always await, uses in-memory cache (60s TTL)
const config = await getConfig();

// Write — validates with Zod, upserts to DB, invalidates cache
await updateConfig({ site: { name: "My Site" } });
```

## Config Shape (key sections)

```typescript
{
  site: {
    name: string;
    description: string;
    url: string;
    logo: string | null;
  };
  appearance: {
    activeTheme: string;    // must match THEME_ALLOWLIST
    navigation: NavItem[];
  };
  ai: {
    provider: "openai" | "anthropic" | null;
    model: string | null;
  };
  modules: {
    activePlugins: string[];     // array of active plugin ids
    pluginSettings: Record<string, Record<string, string | boolean>>;
  };
  aeo: {
    siteSummary: string;
    organizationName: string;
    organizationType: string;
  };
}
```

## Notes

- pugmill.config.json is a seed file only — read once on first boot, then the DB row is the live source.
- getConfig() caches in memory for 60s. invalidateConfigCache() clears it synchronously.
- Multi-instance deployments: the cache is per-instance. For real-time propagation across instances, Redis pub/sub is required (not yet built).
